.UPDATE...
Issued at 904 AM PDT Sun Jul 5 2026

The threat for high-based convection has greatly diminished as the
short-wave trough continues to push inland away from the Bay Area
and Central Coast. Mid/high level clouds also continue to exit the
region earlier than expected with low clouds forecast to continue to
retreat to the coast by this afternoon. However, still expecting
cooler temperatures as a result of the mid/upper level trough. No
significant changes to the ongoing forecast at this time.

